

JavaScript:

	- A loosely typed scripting language.
	- Vanilla JS doesn't support object-oriented features.

TypeScript:

	A super-set of JavaScript.
	TypeScript is a type-support Scripting Language.
	TypeScript support object-oriented features.
	
--------------------------------------------------

NPM (Node Package Manager): Helps in managing the third-party modules such as install, uninstall or update the packages.

	Local Packages:
	
		These packages installed at the application level.
		
		npm install package-name
		npm uninstall package-name
		npm update package-name
		npm install package-name@version
		
		npm install 
		npm update
	
	Global Packages:

		These packages installed at the user level. 
	
		npm install package-name -g
		npm uninstall package-name --global
		npm update package-name --global
		npm install package-name@version --global
	
		npm install typescript --global
		
		npm install @angular/cli@latest --global
	
package.json - A file that contains the meta information about your project such as name, version, author and list of dependencies that a project needs.

-- To create package.json in your application folder:

	npm init

--------------------------------------------------



